reviews.review_text:
Grab a slice of sonic heaven here Good show, great sound.
Thank you Hunter Seamons.

Cream and Sugar only This show gets a bit maligned as uneven. But if you like shows where Jerry is feeling it and the band is tight, then you’re gonna love the highlights from this excellent matrix recording. The Bird Song is reliably strong and the succeeding Let It Grow->Deal is surely one of the year’s best. Jerry’s soaring final solo in Deal (starting around 3:50) is sublime. The post drums section is outstanding too. Try the crispy Aiko and gorgeous Stella Blue, for example. Even the set ending Good Lovin’ is spirited, with a really sweet Brokedown encore as cherry on top. Give it a whirl and see, and ignore the 1981 haters out there.
